# ==========================================
# HOW TO USE:
# ==========================================
# 
# 1. For LOCAL development:
#    - Create .env.local in backend/, web-frontend/, and admin-frontend/
#    - Copy relevant sections above into those files
#    - Uncomment the lines
#
# 2. For PRODUCTION deployment:
#    - Push code to GitHub as-is (main .env files have production URLs)
#    - No need to change anything
#
# 3. Priority order (highest to lowest):
#    - .env.local (highest - for local dev)
#    - .env.production (for production builds)
#    - .env (fallback - currently set to production)
# ==========================================

# ==========================================
# QUICK START FOR LOCAL DEV:
# ==========================================
# 
# Terminal 1 (Backend):
#   cd backend
#   echo "NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000" > .env.local
#   npm start
#
# Terminal 2 (Website):
#   cd web-frontend
#   echo "NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000" > .env.local
#   npm run dev
#
# Terminal 3 (Admin):
#   cd admin-frontend
#   echo "NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000" > .env.local
#   npm run dev
# ==========================================
